&lt;h2 id=&#34;Step3-check-if-your-SSL-certificate-is-in-etc-letsencrypt-live-domain1-com-folder-You-should-have-below-files&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#Step3-check-if-your-SSL-certificate-is-in-etc-letsencrypt-live-domain1-com-folder-You-should-have-below-files&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;Step3, check if your SSL certificate is in /etc/letsencrypt/live/domain1.com/ folder. You should have below files.&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Step3, check if your SSL certificate is in /etc/letsencrypt/live/&lt;strong&gt;domain1&lt;/strong&gt;.com/ folder. You should have below files.&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;figure class=&#34;highlight plain hljs&#34;&gt;&lt;table&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;gutter&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;4&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;code&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;privkey.pem  : the private key for your certificate.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;fullchain.pem: the certificate file used in most server software.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;chain.pem    : used for OCSP stapling in Nginx &amp;gt;=1.3.7.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;cert.pem     : will break many server configurations, and should not be used without reading further documentation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

