&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Enable the REMI repository&lt;/strong&gt; By default, the REMI repository is disabled. The REMI repository provides a variety of up-to-date packages that are useful or are a requirement for many popular web-based services. REMI maintains latest version of MySQL and PHP (backports of fedora RPM) so it is not a bad idea to enable the REMI repositories by default. &lt;strong&gt;Use VIM or NANO to edit /etc/yum.repos.d/remi.repo&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
