&lt;h2 id=&#34;Step-3-Extract-the-&amp;#x201C;opencart-x-x-x-x&amp;#x201D;-zipped-file&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#Step-3-Extract-the-&amp;#x201C;opencart-x-x-x-x&amp;#x201D;-zipped-file&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;Step 3. Extract the &amp;#x201C;opencart-x.x.x.x&amp;#x201D; zipped file.&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Step 3. Extract the &amp;#x201C;opencart-x.x.x.x&amp;#x201D; zipped file.&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Use your FTP or SFTP client to upload the extracted folders and files in the folder &amp;#x201C;upload&amp;#x201D; to your hosting. &lt;img src=&#34;/2014/07/opencart-install.png&#34; alt=&#34;Opencart Install&#34;&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Make sure you have set the correct permissions on the opencart directories.&lt;/strong&gt; For example, for Apache server, default user/group names are &amp;#x201C;apache&amp;#x201D;. To set the user/group permission in Linux, execute the command (&lt;em&gt;Change the Path to match the location of the your store&lt;/em&gt;):&lt;/p&gt;
