&lt;h2 id=&#34;Step-4-Visit-the-store&amp;#x2019;s-home-page-use-your-browser&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#Step-4-Visit-the-store&amp;#x2019;s-home-page-use-your-browser&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;Step 4. Visit the store&amp;#x2019;s home page use your browser.&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Step 4. Visit the store&amp;#x2019;s home page use your browser.&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;Step-5-You-are-almost-done-Follow-the-onscreen-instructions&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#Step-5-You-are-almost-done-Follow-the-onscreen-instructions&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;Step 5. You are almost done! Follow the onscreen instructions.&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Step 5. You are almost done! Follow the onscreen instructions.&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;You&amp;#x2019;ll need to fill in the database name, database username, and password. You&amp;#x2019;ll also be setting up an adminstrator username and password as well. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;Step-6-Delete-the-install-directory-after-the-installation-is-complete-for-security-purposes&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#Step-6-Delete-the-install-directory-after-the-installation-is-complete-for-security-purposes&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;Step 6. Delete the install directory after the installation is complete for security purposes&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Step 6. Delete the install directory after the installation is complete for security purposes&lt;/h2&gt;

 &lt;p&gt;To reset the Hosts file back to the default in Windows 8/7/Vista/XP, follow these steps, as appropriate for the operating system that you are running. Navigate to &lt;strong&gt;c:\Windows\System32\drivers\etc&lt;/strong&gt; or press Windows key + R and type in&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;figure class=&#34;highlight plain hljs&#34;&gt;&lt;table&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;gutter&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;code&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;%WinDir%\System32\Drivers\Etc&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;into the &amp;#x201C;RUN&amp;#x201D; box where you can type commands to either pull up a program or go online. Rename the Hosts file &amp;#x201C;hosts&amp;#x201D; to &amp;#x201C;Hosts.old&amp;#x201D;. Create a new default hosts file:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt; Right-click an open space in the Windows\System32\Drivers\Etc folder, point to New, click Text Document.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; Enter &amp;#x201C;&lt;strong&gt;hosts&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#x201C; for the filename, press Enter.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; Click Yes to confirm that the file name extension will not be .txt.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; Open the new Hosts file in a text editor, such as Notepad.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; Copy the following text to the file:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
